Bonus Gender Pay Gap 

The  bonus  pay  gap  represents  the  difference  between  the  bonus  pay  that  male  and  female  relevant 
employees receive.  Brook Learning Trust’s Mean Bonus Gender Pay Gap is 30% and Median Bonus 
Gender Pay Gap is 35%.  

The proportion of males receiving a bonus payment was 13% compared to the proportion of females at 
11%. 

 
 

